      "source_region": "div.problem-additional-text",
      "text": "[Ba89b] Baumgartner, James E., Remarks on partition ordinals. (1989), 5--17."
    },
    "remarks": {
      "sha256": "eb9df61dd177b0b5478ac024f31cce76d9174f8ffdd3c7cc1c061fae03b590ee",
      "source_region": "div.problem-additional-text",
      "text": "Baumgartner \\cite{Ba89b} proved that, assuming a form of Martin's axiom, that $\\omega_1\\omega\\to (\\omega_1\\omega, 3)^2$."
    },
    "statement": {
      "sha256": "51c6ad7ebfc13b027d2561f3d35b03f518a93d80b1d7a0ea4520bc51f4084620",
      "source_region": "div#content",
      "text": "Is it true that, for all finite $k<\\omega$,\\[\\omega_1^2\\to (\\omega_1\\omega, 3,\\ldots,3)_{k+1}^2?\\]"
    }
  },
